"about open positions"
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Activate:</b> After the quotation is signed, update the Job Position "
"status to <b>Open</b>."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Activation:</b> Once the Sales Order is validated by the client, manually "
"update the status to\n"
"                    <b>\"Open\"</b> to begin active sourcing."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Add to Pool:</b> Select the application and click the <b>Add to Pool</b> "
"button."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Applicants:</b> Track active candidates through the recruitment pipeline "
"for each job position."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Automatic Tracking:</b> This action automatically creates a line for this "
"candidate into the\n"
"                    <b>\"Reporting / Cv sent Report.\"</b>"
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Automation:</b> Each pipeline stage can be configured to send automated "
"emails to maintain consistent\n"
"                    communication with candidates."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Availability Tracking:</b> For every applicant, you can toggle their "
"status (Available/Unavailable) or\n"
"                    set a specific \"Available From\" date."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Bill:</b> Once the successful candidates are hired, proceed to "
"<b>invoice</b> the Sales Order."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Configure</b> client details and grant portal access to the hiring team."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Convert to Talent:</b> The candidate is now a \"Talent.\" From their "
"profile, you can now instantly apply\n"
"                    them to any other open positions."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid "<b>Create</b> a new job position"
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Define Requirements:</b> Input essential details such as target profile, "
"salary range, and job description."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid "<b>Define</b> key skills required for the job"
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid "<b>Document Management:</b>"
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Done:</b> Fulfilled or inactive job position; these are hidden from the "
"website and automatically\n"
"                            filtered out of your main view."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Draft Sales Order:</b> Once the details are finalized, generate a "
"<b>Quotation</b> from either\n"
"                            the Job Position or the Opportunity; both "
"methods will link the records correctly."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Draft:</b> Used for job position awaiting final client approval. You "
"cannot publish these or add\n"
"                            applicants yet."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>External Settings:</b> For client-based job positions, you can designate "
"the Customer and the\n"
"                    <b>Hiring Team Contact</b>. Members of the Hiring Team "
"Contact will receive emails whenever new CVs are\n"
"                    submitted."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Flexible Billing:</b> Customize payment terms within the Sales Order "
"based on the specific contract type."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Generate Job:</b> From the Opportunity, select <b>Create New Job</b>."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid "<b>Go Live</b> by switching the status to \"Open.\""
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Independent Pipelines:</b> While core information is linked, each "
"application follows its own unique\n"
"                    recruitment journey, allowing you to track progress for "
"different roles simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Initiate:</b> Open the CRM app and create a new <b>Opportunity</b> for "
"your client."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Internal Files:</b> Documents attached to the <b>Chatter</b> are private "
"and for internal use\n"
"                            only."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Invoicing:</b> Once the Sales Order is signed, you can proceed to "
"generate the invoice according to the agreed-upon terms."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Job Positions:</b> Define your requirements, website listings, and "
"necessary skills."
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid "<b>Key Configuration Rules</b>"
msgstr ""

#. module: headhunter
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:headhunter.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"<b>Locate the Candidate:</b> Find the new application within that Job "
"Position in the back-end."
msgstr ""

